
[1]apoplexy

   AP'OPLEXY, n. [Gr. from, to strike.]

   A sudden deprivation of all sense and voluntary motion, occasioned by
   repletion or whatever interrupts the action of the nerves upon the
   muscles.

   Dryden, for the sake of measure, uses apoplex, for apoplexy.
     __________________________________________________________________

